In my eight year experience of Horseshoe Lake- this is the clearest and deepest visual reading I have seen.  Last year was one of the LEAST clear. This year has had very little snow melt and spring rain run-off and last year had lots.  These two years dramatically demonstrate how much the run-off does affect our beautiful lake.
Algae bloom present.  Clear- 0% cloud cover.  Monitoring completed in conjunction with zm and swf tows.
Joe Zenk + Xavier Piper in attendance with Gene. First timers.
